'''Vorkath''' (roughly translated as '''pathetic failure/weakling/runt''' in the [[dragonkin]]'s language) is a draconic [[boss|boss-monster]] first encountered during the [[Dragon Slayer II]] quest as the penultimate boss. Created by [[Zorgoth]] during the [[Fourth Age]]'s [[Dragonkin Conflicts]], the blue dragon is one of his subjects that has survived his experiments in [[Ungael laboratory|the laboratory]] beneath the [[dragonkin]] fortress on [[Ungael]]. Despite its phenomenal strength, Zorgoth abandoned Vorkath due to its lack of aggression, leaving it as a 'distraction' for any humans that would stumble onto the island.

Vorkath is considered a [[blue dragon]] and [[zombie]] for the purpose of a [[Slayer task]]. As Vorkath is also [[undead]], the [[Salve amulet]] and its variants will work on him. However, it does not stack with the [[Slayer helmet]]. Vorkath is also immune to recoil damage.

After completing [[Dragon Slayer II]], players may fight Vorkath again, with increased stats and rewards.

