==Drops==
[[File:Vorkath Loot Spots.png|thumb|right|250px|The eight potential tiles for loot to be dropped in. The direction is facing north.]]

{{DropLogProject|kills=15512839}}

Upon subduing Vorkath, the drops will be placed in one of eight different tiles surrounding Vorkath. The spot in which they are dropped are dependent on the player's position after the death animation finishes. For example, standing directly south of the boss (as indicated by the blue marker by Vorkath's head) will result in the loot being dropped on the blue tile marker. If the player was standing left from that marker, they would appear on the south-west corner tile instead, as indicated by the red marker.

''In addition to the 100% drops, the player will also have two rolls on Vorkath's drop table, excluding tertiary items, which have only one roll. The displayed drop chances represent a single roll. Drops will remain on the ground for 3 hours or until the player leaves the [[instanced]] area.''{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1688468997375762432|date=7 August 2023|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/96330|archivedate=10 August 2023|quote=I believe those are 180 mins. This is not universal across all instances, but it's been enabled for quite a few repeatable boss rooms.}}

