==Trivia==
*Vorkath's sleeping examine is a reference to the phrase "let sleeping dogs lie", which means to avoid interfering with situations where nothing is currently wrong.
*Vorkath had a festive override wearing a [[Santa hat]] during the [[2018 Christmas event/Gallery|2018]], [[2019 Christmas event/Gallery|2019]], [[2020 Christmas event/Gallery|2020]], [[2021 Christmas event/Gallery|2021]], [[2022 Christmas event/Gallery|2022]], [[2023 Christmas event/Gallery|2023]], [[2024 Christmas event/Gallery|2024]], and [[2025 Christmas event/Gallery|2025]] Christmas events.
*Vorkath is the second piece of content conceived in ''Old School RuneScape'' that went on to be used in ''RuneScape 3''. Like in ''Old School RuneScape'', {{RSL|Vorkath}} is an undead dragon created by {{RSL|Zorgoth}} on {{RSL|Ungael}}, but was disposed of due to lack of aggression. It was later raised from the dead by {{RSL|Zemouregal}} to be used as a weapon to attack {{RSL|Fort Forinthry}} in the {{RSL|Battle of Forinthry}}. Unlike in ''Old School RuneScape'', Vorkath has all four of its legs intact, due to the technical limitations of rigging a fluid 3-legged dragon.
**''RuneScape 3''{{'}}s Vorkath, in normal mode, has 750,000 lifepoints, equal to 7,500 hitpoints in ''Old School RuneScape'', meaning the ''Old School RuneScape'' version of Vorkath has 10 times less health than its ''RuneScape 3'' counterpart.

